The course was designed by Charles Czeisler, professor of sleep medicine at Harvard Medical School and a specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital, which he believes is the first of its kind in the United States.
He was inspired to start the course after giving a lecture on the impact of sleep deprivation on learning.
At the end, a girl came up to me and said, "Why are you telling me this now, in my senior year?"
