He also said that the prospect of becoming a parent made him less interested in winning the Olympics.
Regular long-running host Kirsty Young has been on sick leave for several months.
Daley, who appeared as a castaway in Laverne's first program, stated that he felt "less valuable" than anyone else who grew up with him because "it wasn't socially acceptable to like boys and girls".
He said, "Until now, these feelings of inferiority and otherness have been the very things that have given me the strength and the power to succeed".
He wanted to prove that he was somebody, so he wouldn't disappoint anyone who might find out about his sexuality.
The two-time Olympic bronze medalist has become a high profile LGBT rights campaigner, and used his presence at this year's Commonwealth Games in Australia to call for more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
He said he got in touch because he felt lucky to be able to live openly without consequences and wanted to give others hope.
The three-time world champion said that falling in love with the man of American film director Dustin Lance Black, whom he met in 2013, "reached him unprepared".
Daley took the Oscar winner, who's 20 years older, last year, but he said the age gap was never an issue.
